4:
What a nice, peaceful day. Nothing
went wrong on my mission, and the
pay was great!
7: Now I can go home and—
13:
Oh, for—hey, you! Get outta here! It's
way too dangerous!
25:
Ugh, whatever! You take that group
over there!
29:
Sorry about that... Didn't mean to get
you involved.
32:
You a troubleshooter? I'll let my
company know what went down, so
feel free to send them an invoice.
36: Huh? No, I don't need any money...
39:
I didn't even do that much... You did
most of the work.
47:
But you did help, so at least take this
business card in case you change
your mind.
51:
It's really not necessary, but if you
insist...
55:
Paradigm Break Company? Wait...
Do you work for—
68:
Creating the latest and greatest in
heroes! AltMeme's premier hero
maker, Paradigm Break Company,
at your service!
73:
Alongside the man who puts the
COOL, ENTICING, and OUTSTANDING
in CEO... Me! KING JOHNSON!
77:
Long time, no see, Alk! How'd you like
the abridged version of my
entrance?
82:
Yeah, it's something all right... It's,
uh... nice to see you again.
85:
Wait, hero maker? You guys make
heroes now?
92:
How about we get ourselves a drink
and do some catching up? I'll tell
you all about that AND our little hero
here.
98:
The Hero Development and
Promotion Division? You started a
whole new department for that?
101:
Surely it's not THAT far-fetched. You
see sponsors listed on the uniforms
of different athletes all the time, no?
104:
And who can touch the hearts of the
citizens more than the shining
symbol of justice! If PBC can carve
its name into that symbol, our
prosperity is assured!
108:
And that symbol of justice is you,
right, Nate?
112: Not that I look the part...
116:
Well, you certainly differ from the
freedom blaster that pierced the
very sky itself.
121:
Huh? What's Bulleta got to do with
any of this?
125:
She's the one everyone's calling a
hero. That power! That energy! That
BODY! She'd make a fine product,
wouldn't she?
128:
Certainly there have been other
troubleshooters lauded as heroes,
but her business potential rises far
above the rest.
131:
So lemme guess... Bulleta said no to
being your corporate billboard, so
you went with someone else?
135:
While I would use more
PROFESSIONAL language... yes. And I
can't say this venture hasn't had its
share of struggles.
140:
Well yeah, considering I'm weak,
gloomy, and ugly to boot.
145:
Huh? What's all that got to do with
being a hero?
159:
But I will say that I believe in Nate. I
am, naturally, her biggest fan!
161:
If we can take her cynicism and that
twisted self-image of hers and spin
it juuust the right way, we'll have
ourselves a LEGEND!
166:
Uhhh... You sure you want to phrase
it like that?
170:
However, at the end of the day,
AltMeme and PBC are both
corporations. They want to see
results.
173: And that's where you come in, Alk.
176:
You've worked with the freedom
blaster herself, so surely you can
help our little hero here shape up,
right?
188:
You've seen how she is now. There's
no one more suited to showing her
the ropes than you.
192:
Or do you hate my beloved hero too
much to work with her?!
199:
I don't think I'm cut out to be a
coach, but...
202:
I could still help out. You know, as a
fellow troubleshooter.
207:
Works for me! And naturally, we will
compensate you for your time!
212: You sure you're okay with this?
217:
Yeah, I mean, I could always use
more cash. Looking forward to
working with you, Nate.
